  <name>Vivid</name>
  <summary>Digital vibrance control for AMD GPUs on Linux</summary>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      Vivid provides precise digital vibrance control for AMD graphics cards on Linux,
      similar to NVIDIA's digital vibrance feature. It offers both a modern GTK4 interface
      and command-line tools for adjusting color saturation per display.
    </p>
    <p>Key Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Real-time vibrance adjustment from -100 to +100</li>
      <li>Per-application profiles with automatic switching</li>
      <li>Multi-display support with independent control</li>
      <li>AMD GPU hardware acceleration support</li>
      <li>Dark theme interface matching modern design</li>
      <li>Command-line interface for scripting</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  
